This paper is about training object detectors, which is a computer vision task, so it is most likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The paper also discusses optimization and training techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new network architecture, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The paper also mentions BatchNorm, which is a neural network normalization technique, so it could belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on benchmark datasets, which could place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
